<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,1837,2044]" lastBlockId="8.[151,1437,152,431]" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="157" pageId="7" pageNumber="156">
The RBINS kindly provided eighteen 
<typeStatus box="[580,678,1838,1864]" pageId="7" pageNumber="156">syntypes</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authority="Knisch" authorityName="Knisch" box="[716,1049,1837,1863]" class="Insecta" family="Hydrochidae" genus="Hydrochus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="156" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="metallipes">
<emphasis box="[716,960,1837,1863]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="156">Hydrochus metallipes</emphasis>
Knisch
</taxonomicName>
, which are part of the Orchymont/ Knisch types collection. The 
<typeStatus box="[479,577,1874,1900]" pageId="7" pageNumber="156">syntypes</typeStatus>
consist of both males and females. I have selected one of the males, a specimen in good condition, to serve as 
<typeStatus box="[544,650,1909,1935]" pageId="7" pageNumber="156">lectotype</typeStatus>
, have labeled it such, and have imaged the habitus, male genitalia and labels of this specimen (
<figureCitation box="[425,505,1945,1971]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1779,1804]" captionTargetBox="[165,1435,482,1710]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1435,453,1753]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 6. Hydrochus metallipes Knisch, habitus and male genitalia of lectotype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3557939" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3557939/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="156">Figs. 6</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[518,570,1946,1972]" captionStart="FIGURES 13" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1786,1811]" captionTargetBox="[168,1423,197,1749]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[151,1435,181,1761]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 13A–E. Labels of lectotypes and neotype. (A) Hydrochus metallipes Knisch; (B) Hydrochus pumilio Knisch; (C) Hydrochus purpureus Knisch; (D) Hydrochus tarsalis Chevrolat; (E) Hydrochus secretus Knisch." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3557953" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3557953/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="156">13A</figureCitation>
). The seventeen non-lectotype 
<typeStatus box="[921,1019,1946,1972]" pageId="7" pageNumber="156">syntypes</typeStatus>
have been labeled as 
<typeStatus box="[1268,1433,1945,1971]" pageId="7" pageNumber="156">paralectotypes</typeStatus>
. 
<typeStatus box="[151,263,1982,2008]" pageId="7" pageNumber="156">Lectotype</typeStatus>
labels (
<figureCitation box="[351,456,1981,2008]" captionStart="FIGURES 13" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1786,1811]" captionTargetBox="[168,1423,197,1749]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[151,1435,181,1761]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 13A–E. Labels of lectotypes and neotype. (A) Hydrochus metallipes Knisch; (B) Hydrochus pumilio Knisch; (C) Hydrochus purpureus Knisch; (D) Hydrochus tarsalis Chevrolat; (E) Hydrochus secretus Knisch." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3557953" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3557953/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="156">Fig. 13A</figureCitation>
): “Bras.Corumba [Matto Grosso] // det. Kniž 
<emphasis box="[970,1085,1981,2007]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="156">metallipes</emphasis>
m. // Coll. A.Knisch TYPUS // coll. A. d’Orchymont: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1817" box="[405,527,2017,2043]" class="Insecta" family="Hydrochidae" genus="Hydrochus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="156" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[405,527,2017,2043]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="156">Hydrochus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
R.M.H.N.B. 15.962 // TYPE // HABITUS/GENIT. DIGITAL IMAGES captured 2019 P.D. Perkins // [red] 
<typeStatus box="[453,613,153,179]" pageId="8" pageNumber="157">LECTOTYPE</typeStatus>
<taxonomicName authority="Knisch" authorityName="Knisch" box="[621,955,153,179]" class="Insecta" family="Hydrochidae" genus="Hydrochus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="157" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="metallipes">
<emphasis box="[621,867,153,179]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="157">Hydrochus metallipes</emphasis>
Knisch
</taxonomicName>
desig. P. D. Perkins // 
<taxonomicName authority="Chevrolat, 1863" authorityName="Chevrolat" authorityYear="1863" class="Insecta" family="Hydrochidae" genus="Hydrochus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="157" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tarsalis">
<emphasis box="[1221,1436,153,179]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="157">Hydrochus tarsalis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Chevrolat, A." box="[151,334,189,215]" pageId="8" pageNumber="157" pagination="183 - 210" refId="ref5281" refString="Chevrolat, A. (1863) Coleopteres del l'ile de Cuba (suite). Notes, synonymies et descriptions d'especes Nouvelles. Familles des Cicindeletes, Carabiques, Dytiscides, Gyrinides et Palpicornes. Annales de la Societe entomologique de France, 4 eme Serie, 3, 1863, 183 - 210. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00379271.1863.11755444" type="journal article" year="1863">Chevrolat, 1863</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, det. P. D. Perkins, 2019.” The male genitalia of the 
<typeStatus box="[908,1011,189,215]" pageId="8" pageNumber="157">lectotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authority="Knisch 1920" authorityName="Knisch" authorityYear="1920" box="[1046,1436,189,215]" class="Insecta" family="Hydrochidae" genus="Hydrochus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="157" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="metallipes">
<emphasis box="[1046,1289,189,215]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="157">Hydrochus metallipes</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Knisch, A." box="[1295,1436,189,215]" pageId="8" pageNumber="157" pagination="55 - 89" refId="ref5572" refString="Knisch, A. (1920) Die exotischen Hydrophiliden des Deutschen Entomologischen Museum (Col.). Archiv fur Naturegeschichte, 85 A, 55 - 89." type="journal article" year="1920">Knisch 1920</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
does not differ significantly from the male genitalia of the 
<typeStatus box="[801,890,225,251]" pageId="8" pageNumber="157">neotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authority="Chevrolat 1863" authorityName="Chevrolat" authorityYear="1863" box="[926,1321,225,251]" class="Insecta" family="Hydrochidae" genus="Hydrochus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="157" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tarsalis">
<emphasis box="[926,1138,225,251]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="157">Hydrochus tarsalis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Chevrolat, A." box="[1145,1321,225,251]" pageId="8" pageNumber="157" pagination="183 - 210" refId="ref5281" refString="Chevrolat, A. (1863) Coleopteres del l'ile de Cuba (suite). Notes, synonymies et descriptions d'especes Nouvelles. Familles des Cicindeletes, Carabiques, Dytiscides, Gyrinides et Palpicornes. Annales de la Societe entomologique de France, 4 eme Serie, 3, 1863, 183 - 210. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00379271.1863.11755444" type="journal article" year="1863">Chevrolat 1863</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName authority="Knisch 1920" authorityName="Knisch" authorityYear="1920" class="Insecta" family="Hydrochidae" genus="Hydrochus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="157" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="metallipes">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="157">H. metallipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is therefore reduced to status of junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="Chevrolat." authorityName="Chevrolat." box="[784,1028,261,287]" class="Insecta" family="Hydrochidae" genus="Hydrochus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="157" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tarsalis">
<emphasis box="[784,902,261,287]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="157">H. tarsalis</emphasis>
Chevrolat.
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="157" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,152,431]" pageId="8" pageNumber="157">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,297,323]" pageId="8" pageNumber="157">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Oliva, A." box="[321,464,297,323]" pageId="8" pageNumber="157" pagination="87 - 104" refId="ref6088" refString="Oliva, A. (1992) The species of Hydrochus (Coleoptera; Hydrophiloidea; Hydrochidae) described from South America. Bulletin et annales de la Societe royale belge d'entomologie, 128, 87 - 104." type="journal article" year="1992">Oliva (1992)</bibRefCitation>
published a drawing of the male genitalia of, supposedly, 
<taxonomicName box="[1110,1259,297,323]" class="Insecta" family="Hydrochidae" genus="Hydrochus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="157" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="metallipes">
<emphasis box="[1110,1259,297,323]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="157">H. metallipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The parameres are depicted as having a more pronounced enlargement of the medial margin than is present in the 
<typeStatus box="[1266,1372,333,359]" pageId="8" pageNumber="157">lectotype</typeStatus>
, or in all specimens of 
<taxonomicName box="[339,456,369,395]" class="Insecta" family="Hydrochidae" genus="Hydrochus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="157" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tarsalis">
<emphasis box="[339,456,369,395]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="157">H. tarsalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for which the male genitalia have been examined. 
<bibRefCitation author="Oliva, A." box="[1022,1166,369,395]" pageId="8" pageNumber="157" pagination="87 - 104" refId="ref6088" refString="Oliva, A. (1992) The species of Hydrochus (Coleoptera; Hydrophiloidea; Hydrochidae) described from South America. Bulletin et annales de la Societe royale belge d'entomologie, 128, 87 - 104." type="journal article" year="1992">Oliva (1992)</bibRefCitation>
did not give the locality data of the specimen that was used to make the drawing.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
